To claim that the top sheet is a universal element of bedding is incorrect, and somewhat US-centric. Much of Europe uses only a duvet with a duvet cover. The top sheet is culturally specific, so I tempered that claim by adding "or instead of," and removing the "always" that started the sentence. It's almost always a bad idea to claim that something is "always" one way! :)
